properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued February 17 at 7:56PM AKST until February 18 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blizzard conditions expected. Blowing snow may reduce
visibilities to one quarter mile or less at times.
Southeasterly winds around 20 mph will gust between 40 to 50
mph.

* WHERE...Northeast Prince William Sound.

* WHEN...From 3 AM to noon AKST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Areas of blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility making travel difficult.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Total snow accumulations of 3 to 7 inches.
properties.instruction:
A Blizzard Warning means severe winter weather conditions are
expected or occurring. Falling and blowing snow with strong winds
and poor visibilities are likely. This will lead to whiteout
conditions, making travel very hazardous. If you must travel,
have a winter survival kit with you.If you get stranded, stay
with your vehicle.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM TO NOON AKST TUESDAY THROUGH THOMPSON PASS
